                        First we need to decide what pages you want for your site. Let's start with the standard pages first. A home page is automatically included, but there are two
                        other pages as well. First is the About page. This is mainly used to inform your viewers a little more about your company and the people that make it up. This page
                        can hold up to 6 elements of both Text and pictures as well. Special features can also be added later the bottom of the page. Would you like include an About page?
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="checkbox">
                    <label style="font-size:large">
                        <input asp-for="About" /> @Html.DisplayNameFor(model => model.About)
                    </label>
